reviews.text: We've been regular patrons of this restaurant for many years and today was the first time we've seen it at full capacity.  Their food quality has always been good and I believe they have actually improved over the years. The skewers are very tasty and done perfectly. Sushi was fresh. The service was pretty standard and nothing to complain (or write home) about. Pricing was also pretty standard and fair. A good atmosphere and a great restaurant at cyberport that has gone through the test of time. Highly recommended.
Here is in Cyberport, not bad Japanese cuisine. The service is required to improve with more energy and hardworking. I highly recommended several dishes: 鰻魚露筍卷、餃子雞翼、燒粟米、炸雞軟骨
Foods are fresh and delicious. Reasonable price. Environment okay
Amazing, been here many times! Never fails to deliver
Didn't try fish,  ordered the noodle hot pot and some dishes. not as expensive as I imagined. And quality not bad.

reviews.text: Such a large mall but so empty. Restaurants are limited, shops are boring. The only good thing is the cinema and that's not enough to draw people in during the weekends. Nothing has been done to vitalize the place.
Came here for a conference. Nice environment but the location is far from downtown.
The worlds worst utilised shopping mall is now even worse as a low quality esports venue that doesn’t cater to local residents needs in any respect. Management must be living on a different planet.
Spacious enough but shopping variety are very limited
Decent mall but very creapy, that vibes towards the max on weekdays & stormy weather. It suddenly becomes a mall with weird things happen.
